snippet.textDisplay: This is wonderful. But Coke Studio you tend to be a little too heavy on Drums and electronic guitars in most songs. It get a little cacophonic at times and makes it difficult to follow the nuances of the song. Essentially it is more of a display of the musical ability of the composer than the song it self. Very common in live performances where musicians are vying to be louder than the singers rather than supporting them. Some songs can be better off without the Fusion twist...
snippet.textOriginal: This is wonderful. But Coke Studio you tend to be a little too heavy on Drums and electronic guitars in most songs. It get a little cacophonic at times and makes it difficult to follow the nuances of the song. Essentially it is more of a display of the musical ability of the composer than the song it self. Very common in live performances where musicians are vying to be louder than the singers rather than supporting them. Some songs can be better off without the Fusion twist...
